body:
By far the easiest and most important lane. But that means nothing for OCEtards.

#1 UNDERSTANDING MATCH-UP

&quot;Hey, Malph, [INSERT ONE-DIMENSIONAL, EARLY-KILL-DEPENDENT, COMPLETELY-NULLIFIABLE-WITH-A-BIT-OF-MACRO-PLAY CHAMP NAME HERE] is useless if you don&#039;t feed and snowball them. Feel free to fall behind on CS, we don&#039;t mind. Just keep up in levels and try to keep your turret somewhat healthy. You will be much more useful come mid-game, given you haven&#039;t given [INSERT ONE-DIMENSIONAL, EARLY-KILL-DEPENDENT, COMPLETELY-NULLIFIABLE-WITH-A-BIT-OF-MACRO-PLAY CHAMP NAME HERE] the capacity to 3v1 in mid-game or just completely swing a team-fight singlehandedly.&quot;

&quot;Okay, I&#039;ll try.&quot;

&quot;Not try - do. Like, no-one will judge you for being behind in CS. Just don&#039;t give up levels and kills. Try not to let the turret bounce waves if possible - but that&#039;s an afterthought. That is [INSERT ONE-DIMENSIONAL, EARLY-KILL-DEPENDENT, COMPLETELY-NULLIFIABLE-WITH-A-BIT-OF-MACRO-PLAY CHAMP NAME HERE]&#039;s one win condition.

&quot;Sorry, I gave FB. I really wanted that cannon minion.&quot;

**Five minutes later**

&quot;Sorry... wow, he/she is so strong... I just wanted to trade a bit. Jungle, can I get a gank?&quot;

&quot;[INSERT ONE-DIMENSIONAL, EARLY-KILL-DEPENDENT, COMPLETELY-NULLIFIABLE-WITH-A-BIT-OF-MACRO-PLAY CHAMP NAME HERE] can probably 2v1. He/she is level 10, we&#039;re level 7...&quot;

#2 MAP AWARENESS

&quot;Hey, Malph, I got a cheeky ward behind their bot lane. We&#039;ll turn the aggression on. Come in when you see them commit.&quot;

**Minute after no TP play has been made**

&quot;Sorry! I didn&#039;t see the ward! I didn&#039;t know what you meant by &#039;behind their bot lane&#039;.&quot;
